<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="24" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
Morphometrics of the specimens obtained here generally agree with those of the type specimens and topotype specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="Lamberti, F" journalOrPublisher="Nematologia Mediterranea" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" pagination="311 - 326" title="Relationship between Xiphinema brevicolle and X. diffusum with a redescripiton of X. brevicolle and descriptions of three new species of Xiphinema (Nematoda: Dorylaimida)." volume="19" year="1992">Lamberti et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Luc, M" journalOrPublisher="Fundamental and Applied Nematology" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" pagination="475 - 490" title="The Xiphinema americanum-group (Nematoda: Longidoridae). 2. Observations on Xiphinema brevicollum Lordello &amp; da Costa, 1961 and comments on the group." volume="21" year="1998">Luc et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
) of the species (Table 2). No male was detected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="24" type="nomenclatorial note">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Nomenclatorial note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
The emended name of this species, 
<taxonomicName class="Adenophorea" family="Longidoridae" genus="Xiphinema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xiphinema brevicollum" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="brevicollum">Xiphinema brevicollum</taxonomicName>
, was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Luc, M" journalOrPublisher="Fundamental and Applied Nematology" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" pagination="475 - 490" title="The Xiphinema americanum-group (Nematoda: Longidoridae). 2. Observations on Xiphinema brevicollum Lordello &amp; da Costa, 1961 and comments on the group." volume="21" year="1998">Luc et al. (1998)</bibRefCitation>
and used in many works to date. 
<bibRefCitation author="Monteiro, AR" journalOrPublisher="Nematologia Brasileira" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 2" title="Nomenclatorial note on Xiphinema brevicolle Lordello &amp; Costa, 1961 (Nematoda: Longidoridae)." volume="34" year="2010">Monteiro (2010)</bibRefCitation>
claimed that the correct species name is 
<taxonomicName class="Adenophorea" family="Longidoridae" genus="Xiphinema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xiphinema brevicolle" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="brevicolle">Xiphinema brevicolle</taxonomicName>
Lordello et Costa, 1961, and should have been preserved unaltered. We support the claim by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monteiro, AR" journalOrPublisher="Nematologia Brasileira" pageId="7" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 2" title="Nomenclatorial note on Xiphinema brevicolle Lordello &amp; Costa, 1961 (Nematoda: Longidoridae)." volume="34" year="2010">Monteiro (2010)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Adenophorea" family="Longidoridae" genus="Xiphinema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xiphinema brevicolle" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="brevicolle">Xiphinema brevicolle</taxonomicName>
is used here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
